result.execSummary:
The defendant David W Wachholz was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Interfere w/Fire Fighting-Alarm/Fighters, a class I felony, Wisconsin Statutes 941.12(1).
  • Bail Jumping-Felony, a class H felony, Wisconsin Statutes 946.49(1)(b).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

11:33 a.m.  State by Special Prosecutor Attorney Peter Hahn.  Defendant present, in custody, with Attorney Todd Snow.

Attorney Hahn recites the agreement - defendant plea to count 1 on 2014CF20 and one county of bail jumping.  DRI 2013CF117.  Dismiss 2014CF16.  Requests restitution in the amount of $1,267.38.  Attorney Snow concurs.  Defendant concurs.

Court goes over the plea questionnaire with the defendant.  Court goes over constitutional rights with the defendant - waived.  Court goes over the elements of the offense.  Court instructs regarding the maximum penalties.  Court instructs regarding deportation.  Court instructs regarding felony prohibitions.  Counsel indicate the remaining counts on 2014CF20 are to be DRI.  

Defendant enters a plea of NO CONTEST.  Court finds each plea is made freely, voluntarily, intelligently, and understandingly.  Court finds there is a factual basis to support the plea.  Court finds the defendant on 2014CF20 to counts 1 and 3.  Court DRI balance counts on 2014CF20 - Court states count 2 was previously dismissed.  Court DRI 2013CF117.  Court dismisses 2014CF16.  Court orders a judgment of conviction be entered today.  Attorney Hahn confirms compliance with any victim/witness rights.  Statement by Walter Belfeuil.  Sentencing argument by Attorney Hahn.  Sentencing argument by Attorney Snow.  No statement by the defendant.

EACH COUNT:
Court orders SWD and places the defendant on 36 months probation to be concurrent with any other sentence the defendant is currently serviing.
CONDITIONS OF PROBATION:
Maintain absolute sobriety - not to possess/consume any alcohol, illegal drugs, or prescription drugs without a valid presription.
Not to possess any burning or any incendiary devices.
Not to go on any premises that is licensed to sell alchool by-the-drink.
Abide with all other rules/recommendations as imposed by the supervising agent.
Pay court costs.
